{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nExisting stores must learn they are behind the registry without hot-path cost — Rails\n`CheckPending` for a School-B registry: compare applied-set to registry ids, nudge on write\nactivity, cheaply, rate-limited, never breaking a write.\n\n## What\nRead `.ensure-applied` (WS1 owns the format: JSON array) and compute `pending = registry ids − applied_ids`; when the file is absent OR unreadable/garbage, the applied set is EMPTY so `pending` = all registry ids (a pre-feature store is genuinely behind) — the cached value is therefore True and the hint fires, but the rate-limit bounds it to ≤1 per interval so there is no per-write spam\n(registry ids from `ensures.py`), ONCE per process, cached as a boolean (registry static in a\nprocess). Hook the COMMON mutation paths via `_seam.append_event` / `event_append.write_and_push`\n(create/edit/link/comment/tag/set_*/sign/transition/claim), lazy import. Best-effort, NOT\nuniversal: `compact.py`, `txn.py`/`transition_close.py`, `delete.py` commit inline and are\nintentionally NOT hooked. Emit a WARNING pointing to `rebar fsck --repair` (the EXISTING heal\nverb — WS3 folds the ensure-sweep into it) only when pending AND `.ensure-hinted` (WS2-owned,\ngit-ignored, atomic timestamp; ADD to `_GITIGNORE`) is older than the interval; then atomically\nupdate `.ensure-hinted`.\n\nAdd an `EnsureConfig` section to `_config_schema.py` (`ensure.hint_interval_secs`=86400,\n`ensure.hint_enabled`=true) with the full scaffolding: the `@dataclass EnsureConfig`, an entry\nin `_SECTION_CLASSES`, coercers in `_SECTIONS`, an `ensure` field on `Config`, and a re-export\nfrom `config.py`. The env override is section-derived via `_canonical_env_name`; NOTE the AST\ndrift gate (`gen_env_registry.py`) only catches literal `os.environ` calls, so it will NOT\nflag the section-derived `REBAR_ENSURE_*` var — document it in `docs/env-vars.md` manually.\nThe hook swallows ALL its own exceptions incl. lazy-import ImportError/SyntaxError (debug log)\n— a write NEVER fails on it; ensure no import cycle between `event_append` and `ensures.py`.\nRare double-hint under parallel agents accepted.\n\n## Scope\nIn: `.ensure-applied` read, compute-once cache, best-effort write-path hook, `.ensure-hinted`\nrate-limit + `_GITIGNORE` entry, `EnsureConfig` scaffolding + docs/env-vars.md entry,\nfail-silent. Out: `run_ensures()` + `.ensure-applied` format/write (WS1), `fsck --repair` fold (WS3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `pending = registry ids − parsed .ensure-applied` computed once per process (cached boolean); converged store adds ≤1 file read/process on writes, nothing after\n- [ ] Pure reads untouched; the hook covers the common mutation paths and the inline-committer gap is documented as accepted\n- [ ] Hint points to `rebar fsck --repair`, rate-limited via `.ensure-hinted` (atomic; in `_GITIGNORE`) using `ensure.hint_interval_secs` (86400s); suppressible via `ensure.hint_enabled` + its section-derived env var, which is added to docs/env-vars.md\n- [ ] `EnsureConfig` scaffolding complete (dataclass + `_SECTION_CLASSES` + `_SECTIONS` coercers + `Config.ensure` + `config.py` re-export)\n- [ ] Hook swallows all its own exceptions incl. lazy-import failures (debug-logged); a write never fails; no import cycle between `event_append` and `ensures.py`\n- [ ] WS2 owns two concrete tests: (a) a pending store (empty/absent `.ensure-applied`) emits exactly one WARNING naming `rebar fsck --repair`, and re-emits only after the interval; (b) a fresh auto-init'd worktree (WS1 wrote a current `.ensure-applied`) emits NO warning — asserting on captured log output"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783577741884796001,"uuid":"77efb6aa-5ff3-4cff-a853-c0aa01902d9c"}